Serves 2Ingredients:2 lamb shanks5ml (1 tsp) salt250ml (1 cup) water15ml (1 tbsp) oil1 onion, cut into wedges2 tomatoes, cut into wedges3-4 thin slices pumpkin, peeled2-3 spring onions, slicedQalat daqqa spice blend:5ml (1 tsp) ground cinnamon2.5ml ( tsp) ground cloves5ml (1 tsp) ground black pepper2.5ml (1/2 tsp) ground nutmegAsha's Spice Box: A glossary of exotic Indian ingredients10ml (2 tsp) ground coriander5ml (1 tsp) ground cuminMethod:1) Combine the spices for the Qalat daqqa blend and reserve 15ml (1tbsp) for this recipe.2) Place the shanks, salt and water in a saucepan and bring to the boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer until water has evaporated and meat is tender.3) Add the oil and reserved spice mix, toss to coat and increase heat.4) Fry for 5 minutes, then add the vegetables and switch off the heat, leaving the covered pan on the stove until the veggies are slightly cooked but not mushy.